ermaLink="false">tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5100791158359408086.post-7790814057006623079</guid><description>&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;&lt;a href="http://home.comcast.net/~lmanzo/MBp89.mp3"&gt;Episode 89&lt;/a&gt; - For some reason, the first three full-fledged stories from the Anusasana Parva all center around a Banian tree. &amp;nbsp;They also share the theme of low-caste hunters and their cruelty. &amp;nbsp; Remarkably, in the 2nd story the three characters are all saved, but all three die violently. &amp;nbsp;In the 3rd story, the Brahmin Gautama is an unreformed scoundrel, but he is brought back to life!&lt;br /&gt;
