&lt;br /&gt;
The brothers spend a month outside in the city walls as a sort of penance, and are joined by the great sages of the ancient world. &amp;nbsp;Narada comforts the brothers by telling stories of Karna's past. &amp;nbsp;The sage argues that Karna's life &amp;amp; circumstances were custom-designed to spark this war and ensure its completion. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
We finally learn of Karna's tutelage under Rama Jamadagnya (Parasurama), and we get the story of how he was cursed for killing a Brahmin's cow. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5100791158359408086-107770917477265288?l=mahabharatapodcast.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
&lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MahabharataPodcast?a=-ItQmF70XJo:5rSQV-BvoGw:yIl2AUoC8zA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MahabharataPodcast?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MahabharataPodcast?a=-ItQmF70XJo:5rSQV-BvoGw:qj6IDK7rITs"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MahabharataPodcast?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MahabharataPodcast?a=-ItQmF70XJo:5rSQV-BvoGw:63t7Ie-LG7Y"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MahabharataPodcast?d=63t7Ie-LG7Y" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
