&lt;br /&gt;
On the battlefield, he kills hundreds of thousands, including the entire nation of the Saumakas. &amp;nbsp;Bhisma takes out a large chunk of the Pandava army. &amp;nbsp;If he keeps this up another day or two, there will be no one left to fight on the Pandavas' side.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
So that night, after the battle, they go unarmed to Bhisma's tent and ask &lt;i&gt;him&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;what they should do about this and how they should win the war. &amp;nbsp;Of course, they've known what they needed to do all along, but it's nice to have Bhisma tell you himself and to even give his blessing! &amp;nbsp;We'll see tomorrow if Arjun finally carries through with his duty...&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
