xt episode, and I've come up with a new way to produce the material that will hopefully make up for the limited amount of time I have for this project!</itunes:summary><itunes:keywords>Mahabharata,Mahabharat,Podcast,Epic,Epic,Literature,Ancient,India,Krishna,Purana,Bhagavad,Gita,Indian,Philosophy,India,History,Hinduism</itunes:keywords><feedburner:origLink>http://mahabharatapodcast.blogspot.com/2010/04/episode-17-cut-baby-in-half.html</feedburner:origLink><enclosure url="http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/MahabharataPodcast/~5/meAvQQXifNc/MBp17.mp3" length="7054986" type="audio/mpeg" /><feedburner:origEnclosureLink>http://home.comcast.net/~mahabharatapodcast/MBp17.mp3</feedburner:origEnclosureLink></item><item><title>Episode 16 - Don't Mess with Balaram</title><link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/MahabharataPodcast/~3/IReyxFupNx4/episode-16-dont-mess-with-balaram.html</link><category>Rukmi</category><category>Balarama</category><category>Sishupal</category><category>Rukmini</category><category>Krishna</category><category>Jarasandh</category><author>mahabharatapodcast@comcast.net (Lawrence Manzo)</author><pubDate>Sun, 24 Oct 2010 22:17:52 PDT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5100791158359408086.post-4734837880062743537</guid><description>&lt;a href="http://home.comcast.net/~mahabharatapodcast/MBp16.mp3"&gt;Episode 16&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;- This is the final installment of the "Krishna Episodes", where I've covered Krishna's back story up to and beyond the point when the Pandavas met him in Panchala.&amp;nbsp; There are still some interesting details in the Bhagavata Purana which I want to compare with later events in the Mahabharata, so I'm not completely done with that book, but for the upcoming episodes, we'll get back to the Mahabharata and see what the Pandavas do next.&lt;br /&gt;
