&lt;br /&gt;
When the battle is about to commence, the master of ceremonies asks him to recite his lineage.&amp;nbsp; Karna reveals that he is from a lower class, so Duryodhana rectifies the situation by making him King of Anga.&amp;nbsp; The day is over by then, so nothing is settled between Karna and Arjuna. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Later, Duryodhana schemes to have the Pandavas sent to a neigboring town, and has a house built for them that is highly flammable.&amp;nbsp; The house burns down, but the boys escape with their mother.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;While in the woods,&amp;nbsp;there is a brief episode where Bhima fights with a Rakshasa and kills him.&amp;nbsp; Bhima marries the Ogre's sister and fathers a powerful half-breed son.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The brothers then wander off incognito, until they settle down in a small town called Ekachakra.&amp;nbsp; We leave them there until the next episode!&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5100791158359408086-3396277809516509323?l=mahabharatapodcast.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
